==English==

===Pronunciation===

*{{AHD|plās'nām}}
*{{IPA|/ˈpleɪsːneɪm/}}

===Etymology===

An amalgamation of place, from Old English ''place'', open space, from French ''place'', from Latin ''platea'', ''plaza'', from PIE ''*plat'', and name, from Old English ''nama'' from Proto-Germanic ''*namon'' from Proto-Indo-European ''*nomn-''.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

#the [[name]] of a [[place]]; a word or phrase which indicates a particular location or position
#*''Often, the name of a nationality is derived from its placename, or vice versa.''

===Translation===

*Scottish Gaelic: [[ainm àite]]

